      The UMP-123 is protected by patents granted in Norway, the United States, Europe, Japan and beyond.
    </p>
    <dl class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-x-12 gap-y-8 max-w-2xl">
      <div>
        <dt class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.15em] uppercase text-stone-400 mb-1">Invention</dt>
        <dd class="text-stone-700">Device for introducing and maintaining a port in an umbilical vessel</dd>
      </div>
      <div>
        <dt class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.15em] uppercase text-stone-400 mb-1">Inventor</dt>
        <dd class="text-stone-700">Terje Eide</dd>
      </div>
      <div>
        <dt class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.15em] uppercase text-stone-400 mb-1">Priority</dt>
        <dd class="text-stone-700">25 March 2015 · NO 2015 0362</dd>
      </div>
      <div>
        <dt class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.15em] uppercase text-stone-400 mb-1">Granted</dt>
        <dd class="text-stone-700">NO 338751 B1 · US 10,485,581 B2 · EP 3273860 B1<br><span class="text-stone-500">also Japan, China, Australia and Canada</span></dd>
      </div>
    </dl>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-x-6 gap-y-2 mt-12 text-sm">
      <a href="/patents/US10485581B2.pdf" class="text-stone-900 underline underline-offset-4 hover:text-brand transition-colors">Read the patent (US, PDF)</a>
